// ========================================
// GIFT Format Question Type Examples
// ========================================

$CATEGORY: $course$/Question Types

// ========================================
// 1. Multiple Choice (Single Answer)
// ========================================
::Multiple Choice - Single Answer::Which planet is closest to the Sun?{
=Mercury
~Venus
~Earth
~Mars
}

// ========================================
// 2. Multiple Choice (Multiple Answers)
// ========================================
::Multiple Choice - Multiple Answers::Which of these are programming languages?{
~%50%Python
~%50%Java
~%0%HTML
~%0%CSS
}

// ========================================
// 3. True/False
// ========================================
::True/False Question::The Earth is flat.{FALSE}

// ========================================
// 4. Short Answer
// ========================================
::Short Answer::What is the capital of France?{
=Paris
=paris
=PARIS
}

// ========================================
// 5. Numerical Question (Exact)
// ========================================
::Numerical - Exact::What is 2 + 2?{#4}

// ========================================
// 6. Numerical Question (Range)
// ========================================
::Numerical - Range::What is the value of pi (to 2 decimals)?{#3.14:0.01}

// ========================================
// 7. Numerical Question (Multiple Ranges)
// ========================================
::Numerical - Multiple Ranges::Estimate the population of Tokyo (in millions).{
#37:2
#38:1
}

// ========================================
// 8. Essay Question
// ========================================
::Essay Question::Explain the theory of relativity and its impact on modern physics.{}

// ========================================
// 9. Cloze Question (Fill in the Blank)
// ========================================
::Cloze - Simple::Paris is the {=capital~city~metropolis} of {=France~Spain~Italy}.

// ========================================
// 10. Cloze Question (Multiple Types)
// ========================================
::Cloze - Mixed::The speed of light is approximately {#299792458:500} m/s, which was discovered by {=Einstein~Newton} in the {=20th~19th} century.

// ========================================
// 11. Cloze Question (Complex)
// ========================================
::Cloze - Complex::In programming, {=variables~constants} store data, and {=functions~methods} perform operations. The value {#42} is often used as a test number.

// ========================================
// 12. Matching Question
// ========================================
::Matching Question::Match the programming languages with their primary use.{
=Python -> Data Science
=JavaScript -> Web Development
=C++ -> System Programming
=SQL -> Database Management
}

// ========================================
// 13. Matching Question (Complex)
// ========================================
::Matching - Capitals::Match each country with its capital city.{
=France -> Paris
=Japan -> Tokyo
=Brazil -> BrasÃ­lia
=Egypt -> Cairo
